                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6353: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-31T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 31, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 31—6:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4549. Rumors that Germany will mediate between Greece and Italy are without
                    foundation according to the Greek Minister who believes that Greek-German
                    diplomatic relations will be broken shortly and that action to that end will
                    await the return of Ribbentrop whose arrival is expected today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
